        "cooked": "<p>it seems that original post is for high-security environment, for that i may get those points.</p>\n<p>my use case is more like medium security, and most users probably qualify for that. (even with medium security, whatsapp and telegram are bad as something, mostly because metadata collection and untrustworthiness.)</p>\n<p>some weird points:</p>\n<p>signal messenger is primarily linked for phone number. so if user loses or changes phone number, new phone number owner can re-register. i think that is how it is supposed to work. signal is not supposed to verify who owns phone numbers, only the phone number.</p>\n<p>2fa may be good, and i use it. only totp at the moment <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Time-based_one-time_password\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Time-based_one-time_password</a> . there are bad options as well, especially those which forces uses closed platforms, programs, systems, like google play and apple app store directly or indirectly.</p>\n<p>basically i think additional 2fa options should be voluntary.</p>\n<p>signal is good for many cases, even high security environments. but signal may not be best for original poster. mostly because phone number requirement. if i need something overtly serious, i do not want phone number associated with it, therefore possible security locks could be separate things.</p>",
